To find the average age (arithmetic mean) of a set of numbers, you can use the following formula:

\begin{equation}
\text{{Average}} = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^{n}{x_i}}{n}
\end{equation}

In this case, we have four Ninja Turtles with ages 15, 15, 17, and 17 years old. To find the average age, apply the formula by summing the given ages: 15 + 15 + 17 + 17 = 64. Next, divide the total by the number of turtles (n=4): 64 / 4 = 16. Hence, the average age of the Ninja Turtles is 16 years old.

